this.name: cacheFor
this.description:
Returns the cached value of a computed property if it exists
This allows you to inspect the value of a computed property
without accidentally invoking it if it is intended to be
generated lazily

this.name: controllerFor
this.description: Returns the controller for a particular route or name

this.name: decrementProperty
this.description: Set the value of a property to the current value minus some amount

this.name: get
this.description: Retrieves the value of a property from the object

this.name: getProperties
this.description:
To get the values of multiple properties at once call getProperties
with a list of strings or an array

this.name: getWithDefault
this.description:
Retrieves the value of a property or a default value in the case that the
property returns undefined

this.name: incrementProperty
this.description: Set the value of a property to the current value plus some amount

this.name: modelFor
this.description: Returns the resolved model of a parent or any ancestor route

this.name: paramsFor
this.description:
Retrieves parameters for current route using the stateparams
variable and getQueryParamsFor using the supplied routeName

this.name: redirect
this.description: A hook you can implement to optionally redirect to another route

this.name: refresh
this.description: Refresh the model on this route and any child routes.

this.name: render
this.description:
render is used to render a template into a region of another template
indicated by an outlet render is used both during the entry
phase of routing via the renderTemplate hook and later in response to
user interaction

this.name: replaceWith
this.description:
Transition into another route while replacing the current URL if possible
This will replace the current history entry instead of adding a new one
Beside that it is identical to transitionTo in all other respects See
transitionTo for additional information regarding multiple models

this.name: send
this.description:
Sends an action to the router which will delegate it to the currently
active route hierarchy per the bubbling rules explained under actions

this.name: set
this.description: Sets the provided key or path to the value

this.name: setProperties
this.description:
Sets a list of properties at once These properties are set inside
a single beginPropertyChanges and endPropertyChanges batch so
observers will be buffered

this.name: toString
this.description:
Returns a string representation which attempts to provide more information
than Javascripts toString typically does in a generic way for all Ember
objects

this.name: toggleProperty
this.description:
Set the value of a boolean property to the opposite of its
current value

this.name: transitionTo
this.description:
Transition the application into another route The route may
be either a single route or route path

this.name: trigger
this.description:
Triggers a named event for the object Any additional arguments
will be passed as parameters to the functions that are subscribed to the
event

computed.name: alias
computed.description:
Creates a new property that is an alias for another property
on an object Calls to get or set this property behave as
though they were called on the original property

computed.name: and
computed.description:
A computed property that performs a logical and on the
original values for the provided dependent properties

computed.name: bool
computed.description:
A computed property that converts the provided dependent property
into a boolean value

computed.name: collect
computed.description:
A computed property that returns the array of values
for the provided dependent properties

computed.name: deprecatingAlias
computed.description:
Creates a new property that is an alias for another property
on an object Calls to get or set this property behave as
though they were called on the original property but also
print a deprecation warning

computed.name: empty
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the value of the dependent
property is null an empty string empty array or empty function

computed.name: equal
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the provided dependent property
is equal to the given value

computed.name: filter
computed.description: Filters the array by the callback

computed.name: filterBy
computed.description: Filters the array by the property and value

computed.name: gt
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the provided dependent property
is greater than the provided value

computed.name: gte
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the provided dependent property
is greater than or equal to the provided value

computed.name: intersect
computed.description:
A computed property which returns a new array with all the duplicated
elements from two or more dependent arrays

computed.name: lt
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the provided dependent property
is less than the provided value

computed.name: lte
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the provided dependent property
is less than or equal to the provided value

computed.name: map
computed.description: Returns an array mapped via the callback

computed.name: mapBy
computed.description: Returns an array mapped to the specified key

computed.name: match
computed.description:
A computed property which matches the original value for the
dependent property against a given RegExp returning true
if the value matches the RegExp and false if it does not

computed.name: max
computed.description:
A computed property that calculates the maximum value in the
dependent array This will return Infinity when the dependent
array is empty

computed.name: min
computed.description:
A computed property that calculates the minimum value in the
dependent array This will return Infinity when the dependent
array is empty

computed.name: none
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the value of the dependent
property is null or undefined This avoids errors from JSLint complaining
about use of  which can be technically confusing

computed.name: not
computed.description:
A computed property that returns the inverse boolean value
of the original value for the dependent property

computed.name: notEmpty
computed.description:
A computed property that returns true if the value of the dependent
property is NOT null an empty string empty array or empty function

computed.name: oneWay
computed.description:
Where computedalias aliases get and set and allows for bidirectional
data flow computedoneWay only provides an aliased get The set will
not mutate the upstream property rather causes the current property to
become the value set This causes the downstream property to permanently
diverge from the upstream property

computed.name: or
computed.description:
A computed property which performs a logical or on the
original values for the provided dependent properties

computed.name: readOnly
computed.description:
Where computedoneWay provides oneWay bindings computedreadOnly provides
a readOnly one way binding Very often when using computedoneWay one does
not also want changes to propagate back up as they will replace the value

computed.name: reads
computed.description:
This is a more semantically meaningful alias of computedoneWay
whose name is somewhat ambiguous as to which direction the data flows

computed.name: setDiff
computed.description:
A computed property which returns a new array with all the
properties from the first dependent array that are not in the second
dependent array

computed.name: sort
computed.description:
A computed property which returns a new array with all the
properties from the first dependent array sorted based on a property
or sort function

computed.name: sum
computed.description:
A computed property that returns the sum of the values
in the dependent array

computed.name: union
computed.description: Alias for Embercomputeduniq

computed.name: uniq
computed.description:
A computed property which returns a new array with all the unique
elements from one or more dependent arrays

functions.name: any
functions.description:
Returns true if the passed function returns true for any item in the
enumeration This corresponds with the some method in JavaScript 16

functions.name: compact
functions.description: Returns a copy of the array with all null and undefined elements removed

functions.name: contains
functions.description:
Returns true if the passed object can be found in the receiver The
default version will iterate through the enumerable until the object
is found You may want to override this with a more efficient version

functions.name: every
functions.description:
Returns true if the passed function returns true for every item in the
enumeration This corresponds with the every method in JavaScript 16

functions.name: filter
functions.description:
Returns an array with all of the items in the enumeration that the passed
function returns true for This method corresponds to filter defined in
JavaScript 16

functions.name: filterBy
functions.description:
Returns an array with just the items with the matched property You
can pass an optional second argument with the target value Otherwise
this will match any property that evaluates to true

functions.name: find
functions.description:
Returns the first item in the array for which the callback returns true
This method works similar to the filter method defined in JavaScript 16
except that it will stop working on the array once a match is found

functions.name: findBy
functions.description:
Returns the first item with a property matching the passed value You
can pass an optional second argument with the target value Otherwise
this will match any property that evaluates to true

functions.name: forEach
functions.description:
Iterates through the enumerable calling the passed function on each
item This method corresponds to the forEach method defined in
JavaScript 16

functions.name: getEach
functions.description: Alias for mapBy

functions.name: invoke
functions.description:
Invokes the named method on every object in the receiver that
implements it This method corresponds to the implementation in
Prototype 16

functions.name: isAny
functions.description:
Returns true if the passed property resolves to the value of the second
argument for any item in the enumerable This method is often simplerfaster
than using a callback

functions.name: isEvery
functions.description:
Returns true if the passed property resolves to the value of the second
argument for all items in the enumerable This method is often simplerfaster
than using a callback

functions.name: map
functions.description:
Maps all of the items in the enumeration to another value returning
a new array This method corresponds to map defined in JavaScript 16

functions.name: mapBy
functions.description:
Similar to map this specialized function returns the value of the named
property on all items in the enumeration

functions.name: reduce
functions.description:
This will combine the values of the enumerator into a single value It
is a useful way to collect a summary value from an enumeration This
corresponds to the reduce method defined in JavaScript 18

functions.name: reject
functions.description:
Returns an array with all of the items in the enumeration where the passed
function returns false This method is the inverse of filter

functions.name: rejectBy
functions.description:
Returns an array with the items that do not have truthy values for
key  You can pass an optional second argument with the target value  Otherwise
this will match any property that evaluates to false

functions.name: setEach
functions.description:
Sets the value on the named property for each member This is more
efficient than using other methods defined on this helper If the object
implements EmberObservable the value will be changed to set otherwise
it will be set directly null objects are skipped

functions.name: sortBy
functions.description:
Converts the enumerable into an array and sorts by the keys
specified in the argument

functions.name: toArray
functions.description:
Simply converts the enumerable into a genuine array The order is not
guaranteed Corresponds to the method implemented by Prototype

functions.name: uniq
functions.description:
Returns a new enumerable that contains only unique values The default
implementation returns an array regardless of the receiver type

functions.name: indexOf
functions.description: Returns the index of the given object's first occurrence. If no startAt argument is given, the starting location to search is 0. If it's negative, will count backward from the end of the array. Returns -1 if no match is found.

functions.name: slice
functions.description: Returns a new array that is a slice of the receiver. This implementation uses the observable array methods to retrieve the objects for the new slice.

functions.name: objectsAt
functions.description: This returns the objects at the specified indexes.

functions.name: objectAt
functions.description: Returns the object at the given index. If the given index is negative or is greater or equal than the array length, returns undefined.

functions.name: without
functions.description:
Returns a new enumerable that excludes the passed value The default
implementation returns an array regardless of the receiver type unless
the receiver does not contain the value
